&lt;pre&gt;LGTM1; exciting to see this getting filled in!

On Friday, April 25, 2025 at 9:27:41 AM UTC-7 Garfield Tan wrote:&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

&gt; &gt; Do we plan to add this to WebView at a later date? The usual pattern 
&gt; here would be to introduce an Android API that delegates calls to the 
&gt; Android app developer.
&gt;
&gt; There isn't an active plan for it, but I don't want to 
&gt; exclude the possibility if there is such a request. It is a bit tricky to 
&gt; expose device related APIs because it involves system permission requests 
&gt; (for the embedding Android apps) and device enumerations/selections. It is 
&gt; unclear how much WebView should do on the app's behalf vs how much they 
&gt; need to do by themselves. I'd argue we should learn from real requests 
&gt; before jumping on any decisions.
&gt;
&gt; I suppose we should tackle WebUSB and Web Bluetooth first because none of 
&gt; them are available to WebView, there are requests (1 
&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://issues.chromium.org/issues/40703318"&gt;https://issues.chromium.org/issues/40703318&lt;/a&gt;&gt;, 2 
&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://issues.chromium.org/issues/41441927"&gt;https://issues.chromium.org/issues/41441927&lt;/a&gt;&gt;) and they have been stably 
&gt; released on Clank for some time already. We can set up a paradigm on how to 
&gt; expose device Web APIs to WebView.
&gt;
